(1). \[E(aX+b)=\int (aX+b) f(X) dX=a (\int X f(X) dX) + b=a E(X) + b\]

(2). \[ \begin{aligned} Cov(aX+Z,bY) &=E((aX+Z-aE(X)-E(Z))(bY-bE(Y)))\\ &=E(abXY-abXE(Y)+bYZ-bZE(Y)-abE(X)Y+abE(X)E(Y)-bYE(Z)+bE(Y)E(Z))\\ &=abE(XY)-abE(X)E(Y)+bE(YZ)-bE(Y)E(Z)-abE(X)E(Y)+abE(X)E(Y)-bE(Z)E(Y)+bE(Z)E(Y) \\ &=abE(XY)-abE(X)E(Y)+bE(YZ)-bE(Y)E(Z) \\ &=ab Cov(X,Y) + bCov(Z,Y) \end{aligned} \]

(3). \[ \begin{aligned} Var(aX+bY) &=Cov(aX+bY,aX+bY) \\ &=a^2 Cov(X,X)+b^2 Cov(Y,Y)+2ab Cov(X,Y) \\ &=a^2 Var(X)+b^2 Var(Y)+2ab Cov(X,Y) \end{aligned} \]

\(\gamma_X(3)=0.7\) \(Cov(X_t,X_{t \pm 3})=0.7\) the covariance between \(X_t\) and \(X_s\) with \(|lag|=3\) is 0.7

\(\phi_{33}=0\) \(Corr(X_t,X_{t - 3}|X_{t-1},X_{t-2})=0\) hold \(X_{t-1}\) and \(X_{t-2}\) constant, the correlation between \(X_t\) and \(X_{t-3}\) is 0

\(X_t=Z_t+0.3Z_{t-1}-0.4Z_{t-2}\) \(Z_t \sim^{iid} N(0,\sigma^2)\)

\(E(X_t)=E(Z_t)+0.3E(Z_{t-1})-0.4E(Z_{t-2})=0\) The expectation of \(X_t\) is constant.

\[ \begin{aligned} Cov(X_t,X_{t-k})&=Cov(Z_t+0.3Z_{t-1}-0.4Z_{t-2},Z_{t-k}+0.3Z_{t-1-k}-0.4Z_{t-2-k}) \\ &=Cov(Z_t,Z_{t-k})+0.3Cov(Z_t,Z_{t-k-1})-0.4Cov(Z_t,Z_{t-k-2})+0.3Cov(Z_{t-1},Z_{t-k})+0.09Cov(Z_{t-1},Z_{t-k-1})-0.12Cov(Z_{t-1},Z_{t-k-2})-0.4Cov(Z_{t-2},Z_{t-k})-0.12Cov(Z_{t-2},Z_{t-k-1})+0.16Cov(Z_{t-2},Z_{t-k-2}) \end{aligned} \]

\[ \begin{aligned} &k=0, Cov(X_t,X_{t-k})=1+0.09+0.16=1.25\\ &k=\pm1, Cov(X_t,X_{t-k})=0.3-0.12=0.18\\ &k=\pm2, Cov(X_t,X_{t-k})= -0.4\\ &|k|>2, Cov(X_t,X_{t-k})=0 \end{aligned} \]

The covariance only depends on lag.

\(Z_t\) is stationary

  1. White noise plot

    n=200
set.seed(1)
x=rnorm(n,mean=0,sd=2)
ts.plot(x,main="White Noise,sigma=2")

    par(mfrow=c(1,2),pty='s')
acf(x)
pacf(x)

    Except lag=0, there is no significant ACF and PACF. There is little auto-correlation (dependency) between different time points.

  2. random walk plot

    n=500
inival=-2
sigma=0.5
gen.rw<-function(n,init,sigma) {
  x0=init
  rnum=rnorm(n,sd=sigma)
  X=cumsum(c(x0,rnum))[-1]
  return(X)
}
set.seed(1)
x=gen.rw(n,inival,sigma)
ts.plot(x,main= "Random Walk sigma 0.5")

    par(mfrow=c(1,2),pty='s')
acf(x)
pacf(x)

    There are significant ACF for the shown lag range and it is decreasing slowly. There is significant auto-correlation for the lag range shown.

    Except the first PACF(lag=1), there is no significant PACF. Hold \(X_{t-1}\) constant, \(X_t\) is not significantly correlated with \(X_{t-k} \ k>1\).
